The AP confirmed the contents with two other sources in public health familiar with the teleconference.
The National Health Commission also distributed a 63-page set of instructions to provincial health officials, obtained by the AP.
They were marked “internal” — “not to be spread on the internet,” “not to be publicly disclosed.”In public, however, officials continued to downplay the threat, pointing to the 41 cases public at the time.
In the weeks after the severity of the epidemic became clear, some experts accused Wuhan officials of intentionally hiding cases.
“A lot of people didn’t understand this.”As a result, top Chinese officials appear to have been left in the dark.